PCHA

2025-05-06

pcha.Rmd

Installing Rust

First you need to have an updated Rust installation. Go to this site to learn how to install Rust.

Installing rustytools

You will need to have the devtools package installed…

devtools::install_github("furlan-lab/rustytools", force=T)

Running pcha 

library(rustytools)
## ---- 1. create a toy matrix -----------------------------------------------
set.seed(20250506)          # reproducibility
p  <- 60                    # variables / rows
n  <- 300                   # samples   / columns
k  <- 5                     # # archetypes to fit

# non-negative values work best for convex‐hull / simplex constraints
X  <- matrix(rexp(p * n, rate = 1), nrow = p, ncol = n)

# OPTIONAL: sprinkle a few missing values, replace with 0 (PCHA convention)
miss_idx          <- sample(length(X), size = 0.05 * length(X))
X[miss_idx]       <- NA
X[is.na(X)]       <- 0

pcha(X, 2)
